page: Parental leave in the United States
message: /* Foreign comparison */Countries don't require employers to pay for time off. Ie Canada, it's government benefits earned through a set number of hours worked prior to birth, but maternity leave is paid by the government,  not the employer. Both the employee and the employer have to pay into employment insurance benefits per pay cheque in general, but the amount recieved by Service Canada is greater than the amount put in. Saying the law requires the employer to pay for the leave is just not...
